########### Theoritical and review articles ####################
cognitive processes deeply rooted in body's interactions with the world
6 claims :
body central role in shaping the mind -> not a mind working on abstract problems (traditionnaly mind=abstract info processor/x interaction exte)
Perception/action peripheral input and output devices
mind understood in the context of its relationship to a physical body that interacts with the world

1/ cognition is situated -> :)
cognition dans le contexte env, et implique P et A (input affecte processing ,output)
mem is situated ? construct mental repres from things never experienced?
même si le voit pas tjs ds mde moderne, avt cog pour action/survivre?
non, plutôt cueillette, tool-making -> mental-representation
barsalou : language used by early humans for immediate, situated goals
-> mais non-situated uses of language
-> spatial ognition tends to be situated

2/ cognition is time-pressured -> :) (pressure of real-time env)
-> real-time situated action at the starting point for cognitive activity

3/ we off-load cognitive work onto the environment -> :)
écrire plutôt que encoder 'off-loading to avoid memorizing'
faire mvts plutôt que rotations mentales pour tetris -> pour simplifier
Kirsh and Maglio (1994)
bouger meubles plutôt que imaginer -> surtout spatial tasks
si slmt tâches spatiales, applicativité en cognitive strategy limited
compter sur les doigts, faire schéma en math
-> doing actual manipulation rather than computing a solution savec cognitive work


limit of info abilities, exploit env to reduce cognitive workload
4/ the environment is part of the cognitive system -> :/

5/ cognition is for action -> :) (fct mind=guide action)
-> cognitive mecanisms (P,mem) must be understood in term of their contribution to situation-appropriate behavior
"memory evolved in service of perception and action in a 3D env" 
  -> glenberg(1997)
svt sert action de manère plus indirecte : info de l'extérieur retenu même si pas d'idée de la future utilisation

6/ off-line cognition is body-based -> ? - attention, mais + puissant et + documenté
