CCL : distinguish on-line/off-line of embodied cognition
on-line aspects :
mind serves a body in interaction with the world
-> off-loading info/cognitive work onto the environment.
off-line aspects : sensory-motor resources brought to bear on mental tasks
-> symbolic off-loading (assist mental repr and manip of things x present)
-> internal uses of sensorimotor representaitons -> mental smulation
--> body serves the mind


