###### Spoken language and arm gestures are controlled by the same motor system #######
arm mvt influence language comprehension
neurophy and behavioral evidence that manual gestures and vocal language share the same control system
manual actions play important role in dev of speech (babillage)
système qui gouverne les 2 dans l'aire de Broca
-> supporte hypothèse que hand motor-control system involved in higher order cognition
-> sentence comprehension affected by arm motor responses (glenberk kaschak 2002)
-> on the other hands, semantics can influence movement planning
Glover, S., Rosenbaum, D. A., Graham, J., & Dixon, P.
(2004). Grasping the meaning of word
-> LSF all the essential linguistic properties of spoken language
point of view : gesture and speech = separate communication systems
mcneill 1992 : gesture and speech form a single system of communication, because they're linked to the same thought processes even if the expression modlity differs
--> language expressed by words or gestures controlled by systems involved in the control of arm movements -> supports idea that motor control is a primitive meaning processor (action-grounded cogniton theory)
aire de Brodmann, impliqué dans l'encodage phonologique des représentations en terme d'articulation de la bouche
adjacent à BA6 -> code arm and face movement
-> neurones miroirs : understanding the meaning of an action by matching observation to execution -> system able to receive and perceive : initial communication system in langage and evolution ?
neurons for grasping : taking possession of an object with hand and mouth
-> grasp with the hand while preparing grasp with the mouth
-> can have been sed by humans to transfer initial gestures communication system
-> initially use gestural repertoire to exchange info
observe grasping gros objets, lip opening et F1 > (voyelles et syllabes)
babillage canonique 6-8 mois accompané par rhythmic hand movements + prédit
activations aire de Broca qd hand gestures
CCL : arm movement and speech are integrated by the same control system in order to produce a unique message
language related to arm control
symbolic gestures and speech are controlled by the same communication system, which was primarily involved in arm motor control
this system is able to emit the same communicative signal using diff modalitties, and merge them to a signal with wider meaning

open ? : relation btwn these systems
Kendon 2004 : precise temporization btwn vocal and gestural signal
